news.title: Chandigarh civic body offers two-month rebate scheme for property taxpayers
news.para: The municipal corporation has scheduled the rebate period from April 1 to May 31, though the official notification is pending. The tax rates have been hiked for the first time since 2020.

news.title: Shree Cement commissions 3 MTPA grinding unit in Etah
news.para: The strategic location of the unit, close to railway infrastructure, enables cost-effective transportation of raw materials from Rajasthan, while cement dispatch will leverage both roadways and railways, it added.

news.title: Telangana HC halts work on 400-acre land in Hyderabad till Apr 3
news.para: The ministry also directed the additional chief secretary (forests), Telangana, to take legal action under forest and wildlife laws as applicable.

news.title: Karnataka HC allows ED to investigate MUDA land allotment case
news.para: The ED had approached the division bench seeking a stay on a single-judge bench order that had quashed the summons issued to Natesh.

news.title: Residents of Signature View Apartments in Delhi to stage protest on April 3
news.para: ​​​The residents alleged that the officials failed to comply with both the lieutenant governor's directive and Delhi High Court's ruling, which declared the building unsafe for habitation and mandated DDA to provide immediate rental compensation.

news.title: ChrysCapital partner, his wife buy Delhi bungalow for Rs 155 crore
news.para: The family has paid Rs 9.3 crore in stamp duty and corporation tax for the property, documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, showed.

news.title: US slaps 26% tariff on India amid ongoing bilateral trade talks
news.para: "They (India) are charging us 52% and we charge almost nothing for years and years and decades," Trump said at the White House while announcing the reciprocal tax.

news.title: Gurugram administration approves demolition & sealing of illegal units in DLF phases 1 to 5
news.para: While 4,500 properties had been identified for violations earlier, 2,100 units now face demolition and sealing drive that is set to begin from April 4, following orders from Punjab and Haryana high court.

news.title: Contractor penalized for delays in TNUHDB projects in Chennai
news.para: The 118.53 crore project at Andimaniyam Thottam, ward 126, Mandavelli, aims to deliver 702 residential units using pre-fabricated concrete technology within 18 months.

news.title: Lucknow: LDA unveils discounts to sell over 1,000 unsold flats
news.para: Despite launching a ‘first come, first served' scheme during Diwali, which was initially extended until Mar 31 and has now been further prolonged, the LDA struggled to find takers for these properties.

news.title: Macrotech Developers alleges use of 'fabricated documents' by HoABL to use Lodha brand
news.para: In a statement issued later, HoABL denied the allegations of forgery and fraud, and said it will come back with a detailed response.

news.title: Trinity to invest Rs 1,200 crore to develop housing project in Gurugram
news.para: In the first phase, it will develop 345 apartments. Avinash Nagpal, Senior Vice President Projects, Trinity, said there is a strong demand for ultra-premium homes.

news.title: Lucknow: SUDA terminates contracts of nine CLTCs over delay in PMAY duties
news.para: The CLTCs were unable to support the urban local bodies and find eligible beneficiaries for the second phase. These CLTCs were given the target of filling up 2,500 applications in bigger cities and 1,500 in towns.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to redevelop two societies in Lokhandwala, Mumbai
news.para: The project will be pursued under the state's cluster development scheme and has a project value of approximately ₹1,200 crore.

news.title: Nashik:  NMSCDCL yet to complete three of the total 21 projects
news.para: NMSCDCL undertook a total of 21 projects amounting to Rs 1,000 crore under the Smart City Mission. Of these, the smart city corporation completed 18 projects worth Rs 650 crore, while three projects are yet to be completed.

news.title: Jane Street plans to expand office space in Hong Kong: Sources
news.para: The New York-based firm is negotiating with landlord Hongkong Land to lease two more floors at Chater House, an office tower in the business district of Central, they said, speaking on condition of anonymity.

news.title: Residents of Arera Colony in Bhopal question rampant commercialisation
news.para: A group among them wrote a fresh letter to the chief secretary for action against commercial establishments in Arera Colony.

news.title: Thane civic body collects Rs 810 crore in property tax in FY 2024-25
news.para: Thane Municipal Commissioner Saurabh Rao expressed gratitude to taxpayers and credited the efficient digital payment options and planned tax collection efforts.

news.title: Nashik civic body sets record with Rs 256 crore property tax collection in FY 2024-25
news.para: This is the highest volume of property tax the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has collected in its 40-year history. The previous highest property tax collection by the civic body was recorded at Rs 206 crore in the financial year 2023-24.

news.title: Zirakpur civic body collects over Rs 22 crore property tax in FY25
news.para: Executive officer Ashok Patharia said, "The council received Rs 27 lakh in cash and Rs 18 lakh through cheques on March 31 alone, taking the day's total collection to over Rs 45 lakh.
